The fact that socialism is often viewed as a middle ground between the two further shows the stupidity of your initial definition.<br>
<br>
As for comparing the two, while they obviously as I stated have overlaping sociological effects to discuss them there effects in comparision is to discuss the side effects of one on the other and vica versa, this type of argument while possible is of little real value.<br>
